wfAppnNodeDelete.name: wfAppnNodeDelete
wfAppnNodeDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete the APPN Node.

wfAppnNodeDisable.name: wfAppnNodeDisable
wfAppnNodeDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to enable/disable the APPN Node.

wfAppnNodeState.name: wfAppnNodeState
wfAppnNodeState.description: The current state of the APPN CP.

wfAppnNodeCpName.name: wfAppnNodeCpName
wfAppnNodeCpName.description: Administratively-assigned network name for this node in the format NETID.CPNAME.

wfAppnNodeNetid.name: wfAppnNodeNetid
wfAppnNodeNetid.description: Administratively-assigned APPN network identification, which can be from one to eight characters. This ID is used with the control point name to create a fully-qualified control point name.

wfAppnNodeBlockNum.name: wfAppnNodeBlockNum
wfAppnNodeBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexadecimal digits identify the product.

wfAppnNodeIdNum.name: wfAppnNodeIdNum
wfAppnNodeIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number from the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is included in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

wfAppnNodeType.name: wfAppnNodeType
wfAppnNodeType.description: Type of APPN node, either Network Node, End Node, or Low Entry Networking Node. This node is always a Network Node.

wfAppnNodeUpTime.name: wfAppnNodeUpTime
wfAppnNodeUpTime.description: Time (in hundredths of a second) since this APPN node was initialized.

wfAppnNodeNegotLs.name: wfAppnNodeNegotLs
wfAppnNodeNegotLs.description: Indicates whether this node supports negotiable link stations.

wfAppnNodeSegReasm.name: wfAppnNodeSegReasm
wfAppnNodeSegReasm.description: Indicates whether this node supports segment reassembly. This is only supported when segment generation is also supported.

wfAppnNodeBindReasm.name: wfAppnNodeBindReasm
wfAppnNodeBindReasm.description: Indicates whether this node supports Bind segment reassembly. This will only be supported when Bind segment generation is also supported.

wfAppnNodeParallelTg.name: wfAppnNodeParallelTg
wfAppnNodeParallelTg.description: Indicates whether this node supports parallel TGs.

wfAppnNodeService.name: wfAppnNodeService
wfAppnNodeService.description: Indicates whether this node allows call-in from nodes not defined locally.

wfAppnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing.name: wfAppnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing
wfAppnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing.description: Indicates whether this node supports adaptive bind pacing.

wfAppnNodeNnRcvRegChar.name: wfAppnNodeNnRcvRegChar
wfAppnNodeNnRcvRegChar.description: Indicates whether this node supports receiving registered characteristics.

wfAppnNodeNnGateway.name: wfAppnNodeNnGateway
wfAppnNodeNnGateway.description: Indicates whether this is a gateway node.

wfAppnNodeNnCentralDirectory.name: wfAppnNodeNnCentralDirectory
wfAppnNodeNnCentralDirectory.description: Indicates whether this node supports central directory cache.

wfAppnNodeNnTreeCache.name: wfAppnNodeNnTreeCache
wfAppnNodeNnTreeCache.description: Indicates whether this node supports Route Tree caching.

wfAppnNodeNnTreeUpdate.name: wfAppnNodeNnTreeUpdate
wfAppnNodeNnTreeUpdate.description: Indicates whether this node supports incremental_tree_update, which is only supported when tree caching is supported.

wfAppnNodeNnRouteAddResist.name: wfAppnNodeNnRouteAddResist
wfAppnNodeNnRouteAddResist.description: Route addition resistance is a value that indicates the relative desirability of using this node for intermediate session traffic. The value, which can be any integer 0-255, is used in route computation. The lower the value, the more desirable the node is for intermediate routing.

wfAppnNodeNnIsr.name: wfAppnNodeNnIsr
wfAppnNodeNnIsr.description: Indicates whether the node supports intermediate session routing.

wfAppnNodeNnFrsn.name: wfAppnNodeNnFrsn
wfAppnNodeNnFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This object is the last FRSN sent in a topology update to adjacent network nodes.

wfAppnNodeModeToCosDisable.name: wfAppnNodeModeToCosDisable
wfAppnNodeModeToCosDisable.description: Indicates whether Mode to Cos mapping is supported

wfAppnNodeRegWithCdsDisable.name: wfAppnNodeRegWithCdsDisable
wfAppnNodeRegWithCdsDisable.description: Enable Registration of Local and Domain resources with Central Directory Server

wfAppnNodeAlertQSize.name: wfAppnNodeAlertQSize
wfAppnNodeAlertQSize.description: Size of the MDS Send Alert Queue Size

wfAppnNodeCosCacheSize.name: wfAppnNodeCosCacheSize
wfAppnNodeCosCacheSize.description: Size of the COS Database weights cache This should be set to the number of COSs defined

wfAppnNodeNnMaxLocates.name: wfAppnNodeNnMaxLocates
wfAppnNodeNnMaxLocates.description: Maximum simultaneous Locates that this node will process

wfAppnNodeNnDirCacheSize.name: wfAppnNodeNnDirCacheSize
wfAppnNodeNnDirCacheSize.description: Maximum size (entry count) of the Directory Services cache.

wfAppnNodeNnMaxDirEntries.name: wfAppnNodeNnMaxDirEntries
wfAppnNodeNnMaxDirEntries.description: Maximum Number of entries in Directory Database. A value of zero means unlimited

wfAppnNodeNnLocateTimeout.name: wfAppnNodeNnLocateTimeout
wfAppnNodeNnLocateTimeout.description: Specifies a time (in seconds) before a network search will timeout. A value of zero means no timeout

wfAppnNodeNnTreeCacheSize.name: wfAppnNodeNnTreeCacheSize
wfAppnNodeNnTreeCacheSize.description: Size of the Topology Database routing tree cache.

wfAppnNodeNnTreeCacheUseLimit.name: wfAppnNodeNnTreeCacheUseLimit
wfAppnNodeNnTreeCacheUseLimit.description: Number of times a cached Routing Tree will be used before it is recalculated

wfAppnNodeNnMaxTdmNodes.name: wfAppnNodeNnMaxTdmNodes
wfAppnNodeNnMaxTdmNodes.description: Maximum number of nodes in the topology database. A value of zero means unlimited

wfAppnNodeNnMaxTdmTgs.name: wfAppnNodeNnMaxTdmTgs
wfAppnNodeNnMaxTdmTgs.description: Maximum number of TGs in the topology database. A value of zero means unlimited

wfAppnNodeNnMaxIsrSessions.name: wfAppnNodeNnMaxIsrSessions
wfAppnNodeNnMaxIsrSessions.description: Maximum number of Intermediate Sessions that this node will route

wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionUpperThresh.name: wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionUpperThresh
wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionUpperThresh.description: ISR Session Threshold at which the node is considered congested. This value must be less than that of wfAppnNodeNnMaxIsrSessions

wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionLowerThresh.name: wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionLowerThresh
wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionLowerThresh.description: ISR Session Threshold at which the node is no longer considered congested. This value must be less than that of wfAppnNodeNnIsrSessionUpperThresh

wfAppnNodeNnIsrMaxRuSize.name: wfAppnNodeNnIsrMaxRuSize
wfAppnNodeNnIsrMaxRuSize.description: Maximum RU size supported for intermediate sessions

wfAppnNodeNnIsrRcvPacingWindow.name: wfAppnNodeNnIsrRcvPacingWindow
wfAppnNodeNnIsrRcvPacingWindow.description: Receive Pacing window for intermediate sessions

wfAppnNodeNnStoreIsrRscvsDisable.name: wfAppnNodeNnStoreIsrRscvsDisable
wfAppnNodeNnStoreIsrRscvsDisable.description: Store RSCVs for intermediate sessions? (for network monitoring)

wfAppnNodeNnStoreDlurRscvsDisable.name: wfAppnNodeNnStoreDlurRscvsDisable
wfAppnNodeNnStoreDlurRscvsDisable.description: Store RSCVs for DLUR sessions? (for network monitoring)

wfAppnNodeNnDlurDisable.name: wfAppnNodeNnDlurDisable
wfAppnNodeNnDlurDisable.description: This enables DLUR support for the Node

wfAppnNodeHprDisable.name: wfAppnNodeHprDisable
wfAppnNodeHprDisable.description: This enables HPR support for the Node

wfAppnNodeHprPathSwitchCtrlrDisable.name: wfAppnNodeHprPathSwitchCtrlrDisable
wfAppnNodeHprPathSwitchCtrlrDisable.description: This enables HPR Path Switch Controller support for the Node

wfAppnNodeDebugIpsTraceDisable.name: wfAppnNodeDebugIpsTraceDisable
wfAppnNodeDebugIpsTraceDisable.description: This enables tracing of internal messages for debugging

wfAppnNodeDebugIpsTraceSize.name: wfAppnNodeDebugIpsTraceSize
wfAppnNodeDebugIpsTraceSize.description: This specifies the size of the IPS trace file for debugging

wfAppnNodeDefaultDlusName.name: wfAppnNodeDefaultDlusName
wfAppnNodeDefaultDlusName.description: Fully-qualified name of the default primary DLUS node.

wfAppnNodeDefaultBackupDlusName.name: wfAppnNodeDefaultBackupDlusName
wfAppnNodeDefaultBackupDlusName.description: Fully-qualified name of the default backup DLUS node.

wfAppnNodePdLogDisable.name: wfAppnNodePdLogDisable
wfAppnNodePdLogDisable.description: This enables logging of problem determination messages

wfAppnNodeDlusRetryTimeout.name: wfAppnNodeDlusRetryTimeout
wfAppnNodeDlusRetryTimeout.description: This controls the timeout between retying pipe to the DLUS

wfAppnNodeDlusRetryLimit.name: wfAppnNodeDlusRetryLimit
wfAppnNodeDlusRetryLimit.description: This controls the nubmer of retries for the pipe to the DLUS; 65535 means forever

wfAppnNodeSoloistSlotNum.name: wfAppnNodeSoloistSlotNum
wfAppnNodeSoloistSlotNum.description: Indicates the slot which runs the appn_cp soloist

wfAppnNodeBrNNSupport.name: wfAppnNodeBrNNSupport
wfAppnNodeBrNNSupport.description: Enables the BrNN support for this node.

wfAppnNodeRegisterWithNN.name: wfAppnNodeRegisterWithNN
wfAppnNodeRegisterWithNN.description: Used for BrNN only. Indicates whether the resources will be registered with the NNS. When register_local is selected only local LUs ( not domain-served ) will be registered. The NNS will forward all the broadcast searches to the Node.

wfAppnNodeBranchAwarenessEnable.name: wfAppnNodeBranchAwarenessEnable
wfAppnNodeBranchAwarenessEnable.description: Indicates whether the TG between the local Node and served BrNNs will appear in the topology database

wfAppnNodeDlcTable.name: wfAppnNodeDlcTable
wfAppnNodeDlcTable.description: this table contains entries for each DLC configured for APPN use

wfAppnNodeDlcDelete.name: wfAppnNodeDlcDelete
wfAppnNodeDlcDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete a DLC definition.

wfAppnNodeDlcDisable.name: wfAppnNodeDlcDisable
wfAppnNodeDlcDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to enable/disable this DLC.

wfAppnNodeDlcName.name: wfAppnNodeDlcName
wfAppnNodeDlcName.description: This is the 8-character name given to this DLC

wfAppnNodeDlcState.name: wfAppnNodeDlcState
wfAppnNodeDlcState.description: Indicates the current state of this DLC.

wfAppnNodeDlcType.name: wfAppnNodeDlcType
wfAppnNodeDlcType.description: This indicates the type of DLC

wfAppnNodeDlcNegLsSupportDisable.name: wfAppnNodeDlcNegLsSupportDisable
wfAppnNodeDlcNegLsSupportDisable.description: This indicates if Link Station roles can be negotiated on this DLC

wfAppnNodeDlcCct.name: wfAppnNodeDlcCct
wfAppnNodeDlcCct.description: This is the circuit used by this DLC

wfAppnNodePortTable.name: wfAppnNodePortTable
wfAppnNodePortTable.description: this table contains entries for each Port defined

wfAppnNodePortEntry.name: wfAppnNodePortEntry
wfAppnNodePortEntry.description: The Port Name is used as the index to this table.

wfAppnNodePortDelete.name: wfAppnNodePortDelete
wfAppnNodePortDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete a Port definition.

wfAppnNodePortDisable.name: wfAppnNodePortDisable
wfAppnNodePortDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to enable/disable this Port.

wfAppnNodePortName.name: wfAppnNodePortName
wfAppnNodePortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

wfAppnNodePortState.name: wfAppnNodePortState
wfAppnNodePortState.description: Indicates the current state of this port.

wfAppnNodePortDlcType.name: wfAppnNodePortDlcType
wfAppnNodePortDlcType.description: Indicates the DLC type of this port.

wfAppnNodePortPortType.name: wfAppnNodePortPortType
wfAppnNodePortPortType.description: Identifies the type of line used by this port.

wfAppnNodePortSIMRIM.name: wfAppnNodePortSIMRIM
wfAppnNodePortSIMRIM.description: Indicates whether Set Initialization Mode (SIM) and Receive Initialization Mode (RIM) are supported.

wfAppnNodePortLsRole.name: wfAppnNodePortLsRole
wfAppnNodePortLsRole.description: Initial role for LSs activated through this port, where 'abm' indicates asynchronous balance mode.

wfAppnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize.name: wfAppnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize
wfAppnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize.description: Maximum Basic Transmission Size (BTU) that a link station on this port can receive.

wfAppnNodePortMaxIframeWindow.name: wfAppnNodePortMaxIframeWindow
wfAppnNodePortMaxIframeWindow.description: Maximum number of I-frames that can be received by the XID sender before an acknowledgement is received.

wfAppnNodePortDefLsGoodXids.name: wfAppnNodePortDefLsGoodXids
wfAppnNodePortDefLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successful XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

wfAppnNodePortDefLsBadXids.name: wfAppnNodePortDefLsBadXids
wfAppnNodePortDefLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessful XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

wfAppnNodePortDynLsGoodXids.name: wfAppnNodePortDynLsGoodXids
wfAppnNodePortDynLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successful XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

wfAppnNodePortDynLsBadXids.name: wfAppnNodePortDynLsBadXids
wfAppnNodePortDynLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessful XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

wfAppnNodePortDlcName.name: wfAppnNodePortDlcName
wfAppnNodePortDlcName.description: This is the 8-character name of the DLC which supports this Port

wfAppnNodePortNumber.name: wfAppnNodePortNumber
wfAppnNodePortNumber.description: This is a unique number for this Port on the DLC

wfAppnNodePortTotLinkActLim.name: wfAppnNodePortTotLinkActLim
wfAppnNodePortTotLinkActLim.description: This specifies the maximum link activation limit for this Port. The maximum value depends on the LS Role and Port Type, as follows: Port Type LS Role Max Act Lim Inb Out Switched <any> 1 1 1 Leased Secondary 1 1 0 Leased Negotiable 1 0 0 Leased Primary 256 0 256 SATF <any> 256 128 128

wfAppnNodePortInbLinkActLim.name: wfAppnNodePortInbLinkActLim
wfAppnNodePortInbLinkActLim.description: This specifies the maximum inbound link activation limit for this Port. This value plus next one must total less than or equal to the total link activation limit.

wfAppnNodePortOutLinkActLim.name: wfAppnNodePortOutLinkActLim
wfAppnNodePortOutLinkActLim.description: This specifies the maximum outbound link activation limit for this Port. This value plus previous one must total less than or equal to the total link activation limit.

wfAppnNodePortActXidExchangeLimit.name: wfAppnNodePortActXidExchangeLimit
wfAppnNodePortActXidExchangeLimit.description: This specifies the maximum number of activation XIDs which will be sent before the Port is considered inoperable

wfAppnNodePortNonActXidExchangeLimit.name: wfAppnNodePortNonActXidExchangeLimit
wfAppnNodePortNonActXidExchangeLimit.description: This specifies the maximum number of non-activation XIDs which will be sent before the Port is considered inoperable

wfAppnNodePortLsXmitRcvCap.name: wfAppnNodePortLsXmitRcvCap
wfAppnNodePortLsXmitRcvCap.description: This specifies if the Port can receive Two-Way Simultaneous or Two-Way Alternate

wfAppnNodePortTargetPacingCount.name: wfAppnNodePortTargetPacingCount
wfAppnNodePortTargetPacingCount.description: This specifies the target pacing count for BINDs on this Port

wfAppnNodePortMaxSendBtuSize.name: wfAppnNodePortMaxSendBtuSize
wfAppnNodePortMaxSendBtuSize.description: This specifies the Maximum BTU Size which can be sent out this Port

wfAppnNodePortImplicitCpSessions.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitCpSessions
wfAppnNodePortImplicitCpSessions.description: This specifies whether CP-CP sessions are permitted with implicit link stations on this Port

wfAppnNodePortImplicitLimResource.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitLimResource
wfAppnNodePortImplicitLimResource.description: This specifies whether implicit link stations on this Port should be defined as limited resources

wfAppnNodePortImplicitEffCap.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitEffCap
wfAppnNodePortImplicitEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second. It is derived from the link bandwidth and maximum load factor with the range of 0 thru 255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port. DEVIATION: 6611 mib uses range of 0 thru 603,979,776.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitConnCost.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitConnCost
wfAppnNodePortImplicitConnCost.description: Cost per connect time: a value representing the relative cost per unit of time to use the TG. Range is from 0, which means no cost, to 255, which indicates maximum cost. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitByteCost.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitByteCost
wfAppnNodePortImplicitByteCost.description: Relative cost of transmitting a byte over this link. Range is from 0 (lowest cost) to 255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitSecurity.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitSecurity
wfAppnNodePortImplicitSecurity.description: The security is represented as an integer with a range of 1 thru 255 with the most common values enumerated as defined above. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitDelay.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitDelay
wfAppnNodePortImplicitDelay.description: Relative amount of time that it takes for a signal to travel the length of the logical link. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port. DEVIATION: 6611 MIB, uses units of microseconds.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr1.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr1
wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr1.description: First user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr2.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr2
wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr2.description: Second user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr3.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr3
wfAppnNodePortImplicitUsr3.description: Third user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with TGs to implicit link stations on this Port.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitHprDisable.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitHprDisable
wfAppnNodePortImplicitHprDisable.description: This specifies if HPR can be used with implicit link stations on this Port

wfAppnNodePortImplicitHprLlErrorDisable.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitHprLlErrorDisable
wfAppnNodePortImplicitHprLlErrorDisable.description: This specifies if Link-Level Error recovery is to be used on implicit link stations which support HPR on this Port. NOTE: This field does not enable/disable HPRs selective retransmission algorithm. HPR will perform selective retransmission on data whether or not error recovery is also done by the link level protocol.

wfAppnNodePortImplicitLinkDeactTime.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitLinkDeactTime
wfAppnNodePortImplicitLinkDeactTime.description: This indicates the time in seconds before implicit Link Stations on this Port will be deactivated if it is an HPR limited Resource.

wfAppnNodePortDlcData.name: wfAppnNodePortDlcData
wfAppnNodePortDlcData.description: This specifies the local DLC address to be used by this port

wfAppnNodePortHprDlcData.name: wfAppnNodePortHprDlcData
wfAppnNodePortHprDlcData.description: This specifies the HPR address to be used by this port

wfAppnNodePortImplicitDlurDisable.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitDlurDisable
wfAppnNodePortImplicitDlurDisable.description: This specifies if HPR can be used with implicit link stations on this Port

wfAppnNodePortImplicitUplinkToEN.name: wfAppnNodePortImplicitUplinkToEN
wfAppnNodePortImplicitUplinkToEN.description: For BrNN specifies whether the implicit Link Stations off this port are uplink or downlink if the adjacent node is an EN.

wfAppnNodeLsTable.name: wfAppnNodeLsTable
wfAppnNodeLsTable.description: This table contains detail information about link station configuration

wfAppnNodeLsEntry.name: wfAppnNodeLsEntry
wfAppnNodeLsEntry.description: An entry in wfAppnNodePortTable. This table is indexed by the link station name

wfAppnNodeLsDelete.name: wfAppnNodeLsDelete
wfAppnNodeLsDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete a Link Station definition.

wfAppnNodeLsDisable.name: wfAppnNodeLsDisable
wfAppnNodeLsDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to enable/disable this Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsName.name: wfAppnNodeLsName
wfAppnNodeLsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

wfAppnNodeLsPortName.name: wfAppnNodeLsPortName
wfAppnNodeLsPortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

wfAppnNodeLsCpName.name: wfAppnNodeLsCpName
wfAppnNodeLsCpName.description: Fully-qualified name of the adjacent node for this link station. The name can be from three to seventeen characters. Format is netid.cpname.

wfAppnNodeLsTgNum.name: wfAppnNodeLsTgNum
wfAppnNodeLsTgNum.description: Number associated with the TG to this link station. Range ( 1 - 20) Predefined values for auto-activation

wfAppnNodeLsLimResource.name: wfAppnNodeLsLimResource
wfAppnNodeLsLimResource.description: Indicates whether the link station is a limited resource. If it is, the TG is deactivated when there are no sessions.

wfAppnNodeLsMigration.name: wfAppnNodeLsMigration
wfAppnNodeLsMigration.description: Indicates whether this link station will be used for connections to down-level or migration partners. 1 Indicates that this is a back-level node supporting XID0 protocols. 2 Indicates that this is an up-level node supporting XID3 protocols including the Network Name CV 3 Indicates that this is a back-level node supporting XID3 protocols (but does not include the Network Name CV) 4 Indicates that this is a back-level node which does not support XID protocols. (This is valid on NONSWITCHED ports, and is not valid on negotiable ports.

wfAppnNodeLsBlockNum.name: wfAppnNodeLsBlockNum
wfAppnNodeLsBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexideimal digits identify the product and are not configurable.

wfAppnNodeLsIdNum.name: wfAppnNodeLsIdNum
wfAppnNodeLsIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number form the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is include in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

wfAppnNodeLsCpCpSession.name: wfAppnNodeLsCpCpSession
wfAppnNodeLsCpCpSession.description: Indicates whether CP-CP sessions are supported by this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsTargetPacingCount.name: wfAppnNodeLsTargetPacingCount
wfAppnNodeLsTargetPacingCount.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired pacing window size for BINDs on this TG. The number is significant only when fixed bind pacing is being performed.

wfAppnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize.name: wfAppnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize
wfAppnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize.description: Numeric value between 0 and 4105 inclusive indicating the desired number of bytes in a Basic Transmission Unit (BTU) that can be sent on this TG. This is an administratively assigned value.

wfAppnNodeLsEffCap.name: wfAppnNodeLsEffCap
wfAppnNodeLsEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second. It is derived from the link bandwidth and maximum load factor with the range of 0 thru 255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with this TG. DEVIATION: 6611 mib uses range of 0 thru 603,979,776.

wfAppnNodeLsConnCost.name: wfAppnNodeLsConnCost
wfAppnNodeLsConnCost.description: Cost per connect time: a value representing the relative cost per unit of time to use the TG. Range is from 0, which means no cost, to 255, which indicates maximum cost. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsByteCost.name: wfAppnNodeLsByteCost
wfAppnNodeLsByteCost.description: Relative cost of transmitting a byte over this link. Range is from 0 (lowest cost) to 255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsSecurity.name: wfAppnNodeLsSecurity
wfAppnNodeLsSecurity.description: The security is represented as an integer with a range of 1 thru 255 with the most common values enumerated as defined above. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsDelay.name: wfAppnNodeLsDelay
wfAppnNodeLsDelay.description: Relative amount of time that it takes for a signal to travel the length of the logical link. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station. DEVIATION: 6611 MIB, uses units of microseconds.

wfAppnNodeLsUsr1.name: wfAppnNodeLsUsr1
wfAppnNodeLsUsr1.description: First user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsUsr2.name: wfAppnNodeLsUsr2
wfAppnNodeLsUsr2.description: Second user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsUsr3.name: wfAppnNodeLsUsr3
wfAppnNodeLsUsr3.description: Third user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsCpType.name: wfAppnNodeLsCpType
wfAppnNodeLsCpType.description: This specifies the APPN Node type of Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsAutoActivateDisable.name: wfAppnNodeLsAutoActivateDisable
wfAppnNodeLsAutoActivateDisable.description: This specifies if the link should be automatically activated when the Port becomes active. Should be disabled if CP-CP sessions are enabled.

wfAppnNodeLsSolicitSscpSessionsDisable.name: wfAppnNodeLsSolicitSscpSessionsDisable
wfAppnNodeLsSolicitSscpSessionsDisable.description: This specifies if SSCP Sessions should be solicited from this Link Station

wfAppnNodeLsUseDefaultTgChars.name: wfAppnNodeLsUseDefaultTgChars
wfAppnNodeLsUseDefaultTgChars.description: Indicates whether the default TG characteristics specified for the Port should be used for this link station, or if explicit TG characteristics will be supplied.

wfAppnNodeLsLinkData.name: wfAppnNodeLsLinkData
wfAppnNodeLsLinkData.description: this for Link Address (MAC/SAP, SDLC Address)

wfAppnNodeLsDlurDisable.name: wfAppnNodeLsDlurDisable
wfAppnNodeLsDlurDisable.description: This specifies if the adjacent Link Station is a node to be serviced by DLUR.

wfAppnNodeLsDspuName.name: wfAppnNodeLsDspuName
wfAppnNodeLsDspuName.description: 8-byte name of the downstream PU supported by DLUR.

wfAppnNodeLsDlusName.name: wfAppnNodeLsDlusName
wfAppnNodeLsDlusName.description: Fully-qualified name of the DLUS node which will serve this DLUR Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsBackupDlusName.name: wfAppnNodeLsBackupDlusName
wfAppnNodeLsBackupDlusName.description: Fully-qualified name of the backup DLUS node which may serve this DLUR Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsHprDisable.name: wfAppnNodeLsHprDisable
wfAppnNodeLsHprDisable.description: This specifies if HPR is supported on this Link Station

wfAppnNodeLsHprLlErrorDisable.name: wfAppnNodeLsHprLlErrorDisable
wfAppnNodeLsHprLlErrorDisable.description: This specifies if Link-Level Error recovery is to be used on this link station. NOTE: This field does not enable/disable HPRs selective retransmission algorithm. HPR will perform selective retransmission on data whether or not error recovery is also done by the link level protocol.

wfAppnNodeLsLinkDeactTime.name: wfAppnNodeLsLinkDeactTime
wfAppnNodeLsLinkDeactTime.description: This indicates the time in seconds before this Link Station will be deactivated if it is an HPR limited Resource.

wfAppnNodeLsLinkRetryCount.name: wfAppnNodeLsLinkRetryCount
wfAppnNodeLsLinkRetryCount.description: This indicates for how many times will APPN CP component retry to restart the link station before it gives up, 99 default is forever.

wfAppnNodeLsBranchLinkType.name: wfAppnNodeLsBranchLinkType
wfAppnNodeLsBranchLinkType.description: For BrNN specifies whether the link is an uplink or a downlink

wfAppnNodeLsAdjBrNNLinkSupp.name: wfAppnNodeLsAdjBrNNLinkSupp
wfAppnNodeLsAdjBrNNLinkSupp.description: Specifies whether the adjacent node is required, allowed or prohibited from being a BrNN ( i.e. an BrNN showing its NN face ).

wfAppnNodeLsDefaultNNS.name: wfAppnNodeLsDefaultNNS
wfAppnNodeLsDefaultNNS.description: This field can be set to yes to indicate that the adjacent CP is the preferred NN server

wfAppnNodeLsStatusTable.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusTable
wfAppnNodeLsStatusTable.description: This table contains detailed status information about link stations

wfAppnNodeLsStatusEntry.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusEntry
wfAppnNodeLsStatusEntry.description: An entry in wfAppnNodeLsStatusTable. This table is indexed by the link station name

wfAppnNodeLsStatusName.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusName
wfAppnNodeLsStatusName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusPortName.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusPortName
wfAppnNodeLsStatusPortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusDlcType.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusDlcType
wfAppnNodeLsStatusDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusDynamic.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusDynamic
wfAppnNodeLsStatusDynamic.description: Identifies whether this resource is a dynamic link station. Dynamic link stations are created when adjacent nodes that have not been locally defined establish a connection with this node.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpName.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpName
wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpName.description: Fully-qualified name of the adjacent node for this link station. The name can be from three to seventeen characters. Format is netid.cpname.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusTgNum.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusTgNum
wfAppnNodeLsStatusTgNum.description: Number associated with the TG to this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusLimResource.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusLimResource
wfAppnNodeLsStatusLimResource.description: Indicates whether the link station is a limited resource. If it is, the TG is deactivated when there are no sessions.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusMigration.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusMigration
wfAppnNodeLsStatusMigration.description: Indicates whether this link station will be used for connections to down-level or migration partners. 1 Indicates that this is a back-level node supporting XID0 protocols. 2 Indicates that this is an up-level node supporting XID3 protocols including the Network Name CV 3 Indicates that this is a back-level node supporting XID3 protocols (but does not include the Network Name CV) 4 Indicates that this is a back-level node which does not support XID protocols. (This is valid on NONSWITCHED ports, and is not valid on negotiable ports.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusBlockNum.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusBlockNum
wfAppnNodeLsStatusBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexideimal digits identify the product and are not configurable.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusIdNum.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusIdNum
wfAppnNodeLsStatusIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number form the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is include in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpCpSession.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpCpSession
wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpCpSession.description: Indicates whether CP-CP sessions are supported by this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusTargetPacingCount.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusTargetPacingCount
wfAppnNodeLsStatusTargetPacingCount.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired pacing window size for BINDs on this TG. The number is significant only when fixed bind pacing is being performed.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxSendBtuSize.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxSendBtuSize
wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxSendBtuSize.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired number of bytes in a Basic Transmission Unit (BTU) that can be sent on this TG. This is an administratively assigned value.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusEffCap.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusEffCap
wfAppnNodeLsStatusEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second. It is derived from the link bandwidth and maximum load factor with the range of 0 thru 255. This is an administratively assigned value for use with this TG. DEVIATION: 6611 mib uses range of 0 thru 603,979,776.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusConnCost.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusConnCost
wfAppnNodeLsStatusConnCost.description: Cost per connect time: a value representing the relative cost per unit of time to use the TG. Range is from 0, which means no cost, to 255, which indicates maximum cost. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusByteCost.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusByteCost
wfAppnNodeLsStatusByteCost.description: Relative cost of transmitting a byte over this link. Range is from 0 (lowest cost) to 255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusSecurity.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusSecurity
wfAppnNodeLsStatusSecurity.description: The security is represented as an integer with a range of 1 thru 255 with the most common values enumerated as defined above. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusDelay.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusDelay
wfAppnNodeLsStatusDelay.description: Relative amount of time that it takes for a signal to travel the length of the logical link. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station. DEVIATION: 6611 MIB, uses units of microseconds.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr1.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr1
wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr1.description: First user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr2.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr2
wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr2.description: Second user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr3.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr3
wfAppnNodeLsStatusUsr3.description: Third user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusEchoRsps.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusEchoRsps
wfAppnNodeLsStatusEchoRsps.description: Number of responses returned from adjacent link station. A response should be returned for each test frame sent by this node. Test frames are sent to adjacent nodes periodically to verify connectivity and to measure that actual round trip time, that is the time the test frame is sent until the response is received.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusCurrentDelay.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusCurrentDelay
wfAppnNodeLsStatusCurrentDelay.description: The time that it took for the last test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxDelay.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxDelay
wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxDelay.description: The longest time it took for a test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds .

wfAppnNodeLsStatusMinDelay.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusMinDelay
wfAppnNodeLsStatusMinDelay.description: The shortest time it took for a test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxDelayTime.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxDelayTime
wfAppnNodeLsStatusMaxDelayTime.description: The time (since system up in hundredth of seconds) when the longest delay occurred. This time can be used to identify when this high water mark occurred in relation to the last initialization of the APPN node.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusGoodXids.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusGoodXids
wfAppnNodeLsStatusGoodXids.description: The total number of successful XIDs that have occurred on this link station since the time it was started.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusBadXids.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusBadXids
wfAppnNodeLsStatusBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessful XIDs that have occurred on this link station since the time it was started.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusActiveSessions.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusActiveSessions
wfAppnNodeLsStatusActiveSessions.description: Number of Active Sessions (Endpoint and ISR) using this Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusInvalidSnaFrames.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusInvalidSnaFrames
wfAppnNodeLsStatusInvalidSnaFrames.description: Number of Invalid SNA Frames received from this Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusInScFrames.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusInScFrames
wfAppnNodeLsStatusInScFrames.description: Number of Session Control frames received from this Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusOutScFrames.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusOutScFrames
wfAppnNodeLsStatusOutScFrames.description: Number of Session Control frames sent to the Link Station.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpType.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpType
wfAppnNodeLsStatusCpType.description: This specifies the APPN Node type of Link Station

wfAppnNodeLsStatusStartTime.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusStartTime
wfAppnNodeLsStatusStartTime.description: Time since system startup (in hundreths of seconds) when Link Station was activated.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusStopTime.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusStopTime
wfAppnNodeLsStatusStopTime.description: Time since system startup (in hundreths of seconds) when Link Station was deactivated.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusUpTime.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusUpTime
wfAppnNodeLsStatusUpTime.description: Time (in hundreths of seconds) that this Link Station has been up.

wfAppnNodeLsStatusHprSupport.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusHprSupport
wfAppnNodeLsStatusHprSupport.description: Indicates if HPR is supported by this Link Station

wfAppnNodeLsStatusHprLlErrSupport.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusHprLlErrSupport
wfAppnNodeLsStatusHprLlErrSupport.description: Indicates if HPR Link-level Error recovery is supported by this Link Station

wfAppnNodeLsStatusAnrLabel.name: wfAppnNodeLsStatusAnrLabel
wfAppnNodeLsStatusAnrLabel.description: ANR Label of this Link Station

wfAppnNodeEndptSessionRcvRuSize.name: wfAppnNodeEndptSessionRcvRuSize

wfAppnNodeEndptSessionMaxRcvBtuSize.name: wfAppnNodeEndptSessionMaxRcvBtuSize

wfAppnNodeEndptSessionRcvFmdFrames.name: wfAppnNodeEndptSessionRcvFmdFrames

wfAppnNodeTraceDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to enable/disable this Trace.

wfAppnNodeTraceFile.name: wfAppnNodeTraceFile
wfAppnNodeTraceFile.description: This is the path and file name for the Trace file to be created

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionTable.description: This table contains entries for every RTP connection that is currently active on this Node

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionEntry.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionEntry
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionEntry.description: The fqpcid is the index for this table.

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionName.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionName
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionName.description: This is the local name of the RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDestName.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDestName
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDestName.description: This is the fully-qualified name of the node at the other end of this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionFirstHopLsName.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionFirstHopLsName
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionFirstHopLsName.description: This is the LS name of the first hop for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionCosName.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionCosName
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionCosName.description: This is the Class-of-Service name for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxBtuSize.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxBtuSize
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxBtuSize.description: This is the maximum size (in bytes) of packets which can be carried by this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLivenessTimer.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLivenessTimer
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLivenessTimer.description: This is the Liveness Timer (in seconds) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLivenessTimeouts.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLivenessTimeouts
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLivenessTimeouts.description: This is the number Liveness Timeouts for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLocalTcid.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLocalTcid
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionLocalTcid.description: This is the Local TCID for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRemoteTcid.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRemoteTcid
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRemoteTcid.description: This is the remote TCID for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionActiveSessions.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionActiveSessions
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionActiveSessions.description: This is the number of sessions currently active on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendBytes.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendBytes
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendBytes.description: This is the number of bytes that have been sent on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendPackets.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendPackets
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendPackets.description: This is the number of packets that have been sent on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendSessionContro.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendSessionControlFrames
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendSessionContro.description: This is the number of Session Control that have been sent on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendRate.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSendRate

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxSendRate.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxSendRate
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxSendRate.description: This is the Maximum sending rate (in Kbits per second) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMinSendRate.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMinSendRate
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMinSendRate.description: This is the Minimum sending rate (in Kbits per second) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRcvBytes.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRcvBytes

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRcvInvalidSnaFram.description: This is the number of invalid SNA frames that have been received on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRcvRate.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRcvRate
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRcvRate.description: This is the current receiving rate (in Kbits per second) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxRcvRate.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxRcvRate
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMaxRcvRate.description: This is the Maximum receive rate (in Kbits per second) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMinRcvRate.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMinRcvRate
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionMinRcvRate.description: This is the Minimum receive rate (in Kbits per second) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDiscardedBytes.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDiscardedBytes
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDiscardedBytes.description: This is the number of bytes that have been discarded on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDiscardedPackets.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDiscardedPackets
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionDiscardedPackets.description: This is the number of packets that have been discarded on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionResentBytes.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionResentBytes
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionResentBytes.description: This is the number of bytes that have been retransmitted this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionResentPackets.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionResentPackets
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionResentPackets.description: This is the number of packets that have been retransmitted this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionUpTime.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionUpTime
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionUpTime.description: This is the time (in seconds) that this RTP connection has been active

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRoundTripTime.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRoundTripTime
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRoundTripTime.description: This is the last round-trip time (in milliseconds) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSmoothRoundTripTi.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSmoothRoundTripTime
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSmoothRoundTripTi.description: This is the smoothed round-trip time (in milliseconds) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionBurstSize.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionBurstSize
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionBurstSize.description: This is the current burst size for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSrtExpiries.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSrtExpiries
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionSrtExpiries.description: This is the number of times the SR Timer has expired on this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionShortReqTimer.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionShortReqTimer
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionShortReqTimer.description: This is the SHORT_REQ timer duration (in seconds) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionGapsDetected.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionGapsDetected
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionGapsDetected.description: This is the number of gaps detected for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRscv.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRscv
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRscv.description: This is the RSCV (in hex) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRscvText.name: wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRscvText
wfAppnNodeRtpConnectionRscvText.description: This is the RSCV (in a human-readable format) for this RTP connection

wfAppnNnTopoMaxNodes.name: wfAppnNnTopoMaxNodes
wfAppnNnTopoMaxNodes.description: Maximum number of nodes allowed in the APPN topology database This administratively assigned value must be equal to or greater than the maximum total number of end nodes and network nodes. If the number of nodes exceeds this value, APPN will issue an Alert and the node can no longer participate as a network node.

wfAppnNnTopoCurNumNodes.name: wfAppnNnTopoCurNumNodes
wfAppnNnTopoCurNumNodes.description: Current number of nodes in this node's topology database. If this value exceeds the maximum number of nodes allowed (NnTopoMaxNodes), APPN alert CPDB002 is issued.

wfAppnNnTopoInTdus.name: wfAppnNnTopoInTdus
wfAppnNnTopoInTdus.description: Total number of TDUs received from all adjacent NN since last initialization.

wfAppnNnTopoOutTdus.name: wfAppnNnTopoOutTdus
wfAppnNnTopoOutTdus.description: Total number of TDUs built by this node to be sent to all adjacent NN since last initialization.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeLowRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeLowRsns
wfAppnNnTopoNodeLowRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN less than the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs, but this node will send a TDU with it's higher RSN to the adjacent node that sent this low RSN.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns
wfAppnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN equal to the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeGoodHighRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeGoodHighRsns
wfAppnNnTopoNodeGoodHighRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN greater than the current RSN. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting a TDU to all adjacent network nodes. It is not required to send a TDU to the sender of this update because that node already has the update.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeBadHighRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeBadHighRsns
wfAppnNnTopoNodeBadHighRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with an odd RSN greater than the current RSN. These updates represent a topology inconsistency detected by one of the APPN network nodes. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting a TDU to all adjacent network nodes.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeStateUpdates.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeStateUpdates
wfAppnNnTopoNodeStateUpdates.description: Total number of topology Node records built as a result of internally detected node state changes that affect APPN topology and routing. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeErrors.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeErrors
wfAppnNnTopoNodeErrors.description: Total number of topology node records inconsistencies detected by this node. This occurs when this node attempts to update its topology database and detects a data inconsistency. This node will create a TDU with the current RSN incremented to the next odd number and broadcast it to all adjacent NNs.

wfAppnNnTopoNodeTimerUpdates.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodeTimerUpdates
wfAppnNnTopoNodeTimerUpdates.description: Total number of topology node records built for this node's resource due to timer updates. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes. These updates insure other network nodes do not delete this node's resources from their topology database.

wfAppnNnTopoNodePurges.name: wfAppnNnTopoNodePurges
wfAppnNnTopoNodePurges.description: Total number of topology node records purged from this node's topology database. This occurs when a node has not been updated in a specified amount of time. The owning node is responsible for broadcasting updates for its resource that it wants kept in the network topology.

wfAppnNnTopoTgLowRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgLowRsns
wfAppnNnTopoTgLowRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with a RSN less than the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs, but this node will send a TDU with it's higher RSN to the sender of the low RSN.

wfAppnNnTopoTgEqualRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgEqualRsns
wfAppnNnTopoTgEqualRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with a RSN equal to the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs.

wfAppnNnTopoTgGoodHighRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgGoodHighRsns
wfAppnNnTopoTgGoodHighRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with a RSN greater than the current RSN. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting the update to all adjacent network nodes.

wfAppnNnTopoTgBadHighRsns.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgBadHighRsns
wfAppnNnTopoTgBadHighRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with an odd RSN greater than the current RSN. These updates represent a topology inconsistency detected by one of the APPN network nodes. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting a TDU to all adjacent network nodes.

wfAppnNnTopoTgStateUpdates.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgStateUpdates
wfAppnNnTopoTgStateUpdates.description: Total number of topology TG records built as a result of internally detected node state changes that affect APPN topology and routing. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes.

wfAppnNnTopoTgErrors.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgErrors
wfAppnNnTopoTgErrors.description: Total number of topology TG records inconsistencies detected by this node. This occurs when this node attempts to update its topology database and detects a data inconsistency. This node will create a TDU with the current RSN incremented to the next odd number and broadcast it to all adjacent NNs.

wfAppnNnTopoTgTimerUpdates.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgTimerUpdates
wfAppnNnTopoTgTimerUpdates.description: Total number of topology TG records built for this node's resource due to timer updates. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes. These updates insure other network nodes do not delete this node's resources from their topology database.

wfAppnNnTopoTgPurges.name: wfAppnNnTopoTgPurges
wfAppnNnTopoTgPurges.description: Total number of topology TG records purged from this node's topology database. This occurs when a TG has not been updated in a specified amount of time. The owning node is responsible for broadcasting updates for its resource that it wants to keep in the network topology.

wfAppnNnTopoTotalRouteCalcs.name: wfAppnNnTopoTotalRouteCalcs
wfAppnNnTopoTotalRouteCalcs.description: Number of routes calculated for all class of services since the last initialization.

wfAppnNnTopoTotalRouteRejs.name: wfAppnNnTopoTotalRouteRejs
wfAppnNnTopoTotalRouteRejs.description: Number of route requests for all class of services that could not be calculated since last initialization.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeTable.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeTable
wfAppnNnAdjNodeTable.description: Table containing an entry for every adjacent node. The information kept in this table is the last FRSN sent and received, the status of the CP-CP sessions, and a gauge that indicates the number of outstanding TDUs.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeEntry.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeEntry
wfAppnNnAdjNodeEntry.description: The adjacent node name is the index for this table.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeAdjName.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeAdjName
wfAppnNnAdjNodeAdjName.description: An administratively-assigned fully-qualified name of this node's adjacent network node.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeCpCpSessStatus.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeCpCpSessStatus
wfAppnNnAdjNodeCpCpSessStatus.description: Indicates the state of CP-CP sessions between this node and adjacent network and end nodes. Inactive indicates no CP-CP sessions exists between this node and the adjacent node. Active indicates CP-CP sessons are active using both the ConWinner and ConLoser sessions. The session initiated by this node is referred to as the ConWinner session and is used by this node to send to the adjacent node. The ConLoserr session is initiated by the adjacent node and is used by this node to receive from the adjacent node.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeOutOfSeqTdus.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeOutOfSeqTdus
wfAppnNnAdjNodeOutOfSeqTdus.description: Number of out of sequence Topology Database Updates (TDUs). In a quiesced state, this value is zero. In normal operation, the value varies depending on the network environment.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnSent.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnSent
wfAppnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnSent.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last TDU sent to this adjacent node.

wfAppnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnRcvd.name: wfAppnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnRcvd
wfAppnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnRcvd.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last TDU received from this adjacent node.

wfAppnNnTopologyTable.name: wfAppnNnTopologyTable
wfAppnNnTopologyTable.description: Portion of the APPN routing table that describes all of the APPN network nodes and virtual nodes known to this node.

wfAppnNnTopologyEntry.name: wfAppnNnTopologyEntry
wfAppnNnTopologyEntry.description: The fully-qualified node name is used to index this table.

wfAppnNnNodeName.name: wfAppnNnNodeName
wfAppnNnNodeName.description: Administratively-assigned network name that is locally defined at each network node in the format NETID.CPNAME.

wfAppnNnNodeFrsn.name: wfAppnNnNodeFrsn
wfAppnNnNodeFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last time this resource was updated at this node.

wfAppnNnNodeEntryTimeLeft.name: wfAppnNnNodeEntryTimeLeft
wfAppnNnNodeEntryTimeLeft.description: Number of days before deletion of this network node entry. Range is 0-31.

wfAppnNnNodeRsn.name: wfAppnNnNodeRsn
wfAppnNnNodeRsn.description: Resource sequence number that is assigned and controlled by the network node that owns this resource. This is always an even 32-bit number unless an error has occurred.

wfAppnNnNodeRouteAddResist.name: wfAppnNnNodeRouteAddResist
wfAppnNnNodeRouteAddResist.description: Route addition resistance indicates the relative desirability of using this node for intermediate session traffic. The value, which can be any integer 0-255, is used in route computation. The lower the value, the more desirable the node is for intermediate routing.

wfAppnNnNodeCongested.name: wfAppnNnNodeCongested
wfAppnNnNodeCongested.description: Indicates whether this node is congested. This node is not be included in route selection by other nodes when this congestion exists.

wfAppnNnNodeIsrDepleted.name: wfAppnNnNodeIsrDepleted
wfAppnNnNodeIsrDepleted.description: Indicates whether intermediate session routing resources are depleted. This node is not included in intermediate route selection by other nodes when resources are depleted.

wfAppnNnNodeEndptDepleted.name: wfAppnNnNodeEndptDepleted
wfAppnNnNodeEndptDepleted.description: Indicates whether session endpoint resources are depleted.

wfAppnNnNodeQuiescing.name: wfAppnNnNodeQuiescing
wfAppnNnNodeQuiescing.description: Indicates whether the node is quiescing. This node is not included in route selection by other nodes when the node is quiescing.

wfAppnNnNodeGateway.name: wfAppnNnNodeGateway
wfAppnNnNodeGateway.description: Indicates whether the node provide gateway functions.

wfAppnNnNodeCentralDirectory.name: wfAppnNnNodeCentralDirectory
wfAppnNnNodeCentralDirectory.description: Indicates whether the node is central directory.

wfAppnNnNodeIsr.name: wfAppnNnNodeIsr
wfAppnNnNodeIsr.description: Indicates whether the node supports intermediate session routing (ISR).

wfAppnNnNodeChainSupport.name: wfAppnNnNodeChainSupport
wfAppnNnNodeChainSupport.description: Indicates whether this node supports chaining.

wfAppnNnNodeHprBase.name: wfAppnNnNodeHprBase
wfAppnNnNodeHprBase.description: Indicates whether this node supports HPR base functionality.

wfAppnNnNodeRtpTower.name: wfAppnNnNodeRtpTower
wfAppnNnNodeRtpTower.description: Indicates whether this node supports RTP tower functionality.

wfAppnNnTgTopologyTable.name: wfAppnNnTgTopologyTable
wfAppnNnTgTopologyTable.description: Portion of the APPN topology database that describes all of the APPN transmissions groups used by the APPN network nodes.

wfAppnNnTgTopologyEntry.name: wfAppnNnTgTopologyEntry
wfAppnNnTgTopologyEntry.description: This table requires three indexes to provide a unique index. The indexes are the owning or originating CPname, the destination CPname, and the TG number.

wfAppnNnTgOwner.name: wfAppnNnTgOwner
wfAppnNnTgOwner.description: Administratively-assigned name for the originating node for this TG. The format is NETID.CPNAME and is the same name specified in the node table.

wfAppnNnTgDest.name: wfAppnNnTgDest
wfAppnNnTgDest.description: Administratively-assigned fully-qualified network name for the destination node for this TG.

wfAppnNnTgNum.name: wfAppnNnTgNum
wfAppnNnTgNum.description: Number associated with this transmission group. Range is 0-255.

wfAppnNnTgFrsn.name: wfAppnNnTgFrsn
wfAppnNnTgFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last time this resource was updated at this node.

wfAppnNnTgEntryTimeLeft.name: wfAppnNnTgEntryTimeLeft
wfAppnNnTgEntryTimeLeft.description: Number of days before deletion of this network node TG entry. Range is 0-31.

wfAppnNnTgDestVirtual.name: wfAppnNnTgDestVirtual
wfAppnNnTgDestVirtual.description: Indicates whether the destination node is a virtual node.

wfAppnNnTgDlcData.name: wfAppnNnTgDlcData
wfAppnNnTgDlcData.description: DLC specific data related to the link connection network. Token-Ring - MAC/SAP X.25 Switched - dial digits X.21 Switched - dial digits Circuit Swtch - dial digits.

wfAppnNnTgRsn.name: wfAppnNnTgRsn
wfAppnNnTgRsn.description: Current owning node's resource sequence number for this resource.

wfAppnNnTgOperational.name: wfAppnNnTgOperational
wfAppnNnTgOperational.description: Indicates whether the transmission group is operational.

wfAppnNnTgQuiescing.name: wfAppnNnTgQuiescing
wfAppnNnTgQuiescing.description: Indicates whether the transmission group is quiescing.

wfAppnNnTgCpCpSession.name: wfAppnNnTgCpCpSession
wfAppnNnTgCpCpSession.description: Indicates whether CP-CP sessions are supported on this TG.

wfAppnNnTgEffCap.name: wfAppnNnTgEffCap
wfAppnNnTgEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second.
